dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data relates to critical habitat identification for Roseate Tern (Sterna dougallii) that is included in the Amended Recovery Strategy for the Roseate Tern (Sterna dougallii) in Canada, posted on the Species at Risk Registry (http://www.sararegistry.gc.ca/default_e.cfm) on September 8, 2010. Critical habitat is identified as the entire terrestrial habitat of Country Island (NS), The Brothers Islands (NS), Paquet Island (PQ), Deuxième Îlet (PQ) and Chenal Island (PQ), as well as 200 m of the aquatic habitat extending seaward from the high tide line for each island, with some aquatic habitat excluded around Paquet Island. Critical habitat also includes the polygons surrounding tern colonies on Sable Island (NS) and the habitat extending 200 m beyond each polygon. The Atlantic Region dataset does not include QC critical habitat. It was updated in 2015 to fix a projection issue as well as to highlight all of Sable Island. (Note however, not all of Sable Island constitutes critical habitat. Due to changes in nesting area from year to year, critical habitat changes annually.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The purpose is to support SARA critical habitat Roseate Tern (Sterna dougallii).

Language: CAN (english).

Status of Data Set: Completed (based on best available occurrence data up to the end of 2009), and posted in the Amended Recovery Strategy for the Roseate Tern (Sterna dougallii)in Canada on the Species at Risk Registry (http://www.sararegistry.gc.ca/default_e.cfm) on September 8, 2010.

Dataset Last Updated: October 2, 2015 by Nicholas ShephardMetadata Last Updated: October 2, 2015 by Nicholas Shephard

Please contact David Andrews (david.andrews@ec.gc.ca)for more information on the methods used to identify critical habitat.

Datum: NAD 1983 UTM Zone 20N

Vintage: 2015
